
Objective : Want to build something that integrates with and extends GitHub



Steps:

1. Created an application.

References:
* https://github.com/r-lib/httr/blob/master/demo/oauth2-github.r # code
* https://www.coursera.org/learn/data-cleaning/lecture/gIaQK/reading-from-apis
* https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xCPWRP_WqYQ # A good video explaining how to create an application
* https://towardsdatascience.com/accessing-data-from-github-api-using-r-3633fb62cb08#.40dk13rdr # article based on above video

* Go to your GitHub settings.
* Select Applications > Developer applications tab.
* Pick an existing application or hit Register new application.
* Set a few parameters for your application and get the Client ID and Client Secret
* By creating an application I can access data on GitHub, which is only availale for people with an application credentials
* Then I can use commands e.g. GET() to get Git detaile e.g. https://api.github.com/users/jtleek/repos


3. Write the code

References:
* https://github.com/r-lib/httr/blob/master/demo/oauth2-github.r # code
